comment.author: 63385174@N06
comment._content: The following picture is approximately 1928 by the construction of the Harbour Bridge approach and I would presume this picture was taken at the same time. However, Australia's first non-CBD highrise development started at Potts Point and the Elizabeth Bay waterfront to the right of the picture around 1920 with the relaxation of building height limits and the importation of elevators and there's no sign of any high rise in this picture. A bit puzzling.
